text: Gobarralong is a rural community in the central east part of the Riverina. It is situated about 16 kilometres southeast of Coolac and 27 kilometres northwest of Adjungbilly. At the , Gobarralong and the surrounding area had a population of 52 people. North Gobarralong Post Office opened on 1 November 1876, was renamed Gobarralong in 1909, and closed in 1967. ==Notes and references== Category:Towns in the Riverina Category:Towns in New South Wales
title: Gobarralong
